==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: mandarin orange
<hw>man`da*rin" or"ange</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A shrub or small tree (<spn>Citrus reticulata</spn>) having
flattened globose fruit with very sweet aromatic pulp and thin
yellow-orange to flame-orange rind that is loose and easily removed;
native to Southeast Asia.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mandarin orange tree.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Same as <er>mandarin</er>{7}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mandatary</ent>⟦br⟧
